answerText: Cuhlwch and Olwen[10] ] The story of Cuhlwch and Olwen is one "branch" of this Welsh epic, notably translated by Lady Charlotte Guest.

question: Question: The hero of this story is tasked with obtaining the other title character from the clutches of the giant Ysbadadden. For ten poitns each: [10] Identify this story in which the title hero is given a multitude of impossible tasks; after completing them all, he kills Ysbadadden.
